===Noun===
'''plain-song'''
# {{music}} The [[unisonous]] [[vocal]] [[music]] which has been used in the Christian church from its earliest centuries.
# {{music}} A [[cantus firmu]]s or theme chosen for [[contrapuntal]] [[treatment]]; so called because often an actual fragment of plain-song.
# {{music}} The simple [[note]]s of an [[air]], without [[ornament]] or [[variation]]; hence, a plain, [[unexaggerated]] [[statement]].

